Package cmpt355.project.jvm

Class Instruction

java.lang.Object
cmpt355.project.jvm.Instruction
public class Instruction
extends Object
A class representing a single JVM instruction. An instruction consists of
  • an Opcode (aload_0 or whatever);
  • zero or more Operands appropriate for the opcode;
  • an optional Label if this instruction is the target of a branch.
Although there are public constructors, the best way to create an instruction is usually by using one of the static factory methods (Instruction.new_[opcode](...)) as these have parameters as appropriate for the opcode.

    • computeStackDelta

      public int computeStackDelta()
      Calculates the stack delta of this instruction. For most instructions this is a fixed property of the opcode (e.g. aload_0 always increases the stack size by 1) and can be obtained from Opcode.getStackDelta(), but for some (for example Opcode.getfield) it varies based on the operand. This method calculates if necessary and then returns the stack delta for any kind of instruction.
